{{fbdoc item="title" value="Compiler Option: -lang"}}----
Provides ""QuickBASIC"" or backward compatibility

{{fbdoc item="syntax"}}##
	**-lang** //dialect//
##
{{fbdoc item="param"}}
	##//dialect//##
		The dialect to use in compilation, one of ##**fb**## (default), ##**qb**## or ##**deprecated**##.

{{fbdoc item="desc"}}
	The ##-lang## compiler option changes the way source code is interpreted, and is meant as a tool to users wanting traditional QuickBASIC-like behavior, or behavior deprecated from previous versions of ""FreeBASIC"".

	The intrinsic macro ##[[KeyPgDdfblang __FB_LANG__]]## is set to the string name of the dialect specified on the command line, or ##"fb"## by default.

	To learn more about the differences between each of these language dialects, see [[CompilerDialects Compiler Dialects]].

	{{fbdoc item="subsect" value="fb"}}
	
		This is the default dialect, and allows compilation of source code adhering to the most recent version of the ""FreeBASIC"" language.

	{{fbdoc item="subsect" value="qb"}}
	
		This dialect provides support for traditional ""QuickBASIC"" programming and commands.

	{{fbdoc item="subsect" value="deprecated"}}
	
		This dialect is for backward compatibility with previous versions of ""FreeBASIC"", however, this dialect may not exist in future versions.

